---
const qs = [
  {
    q: "Why fractional and not just a full-time EA hire?",
    a: "Three reasons. First, you're not 100% utilized yet, and a fractional EA sized to your actual need is half the cost of a misjudged full-time hire. Second, senior EA hiring takes 8 to 12 weeks and most searches run longer; fractional starts next week. Third, if you're unsure what the role should look like, a fractional engagement becomes a working job description for whoever you eventually hire.",
  },
  {
    q: "Why you and not a $50 an hour virtual assistant?",
    a: "VAs execute tasks. I design the system the VA (or junior EA) will execute. A VA can book a flight. I can build the pre-trip briefing template, the priority-ranked calendar logic, the post-travel debrief, and the comms protocol with your investor relations team. Two different products. If your need is the first, hire a VA. If it's the second, hire me.",
  },
  {
    q: "How do you handle confidentiality?",
    a: "NDA by default before any engagement starts. At Immunovant I managed pre-IPO materials, FDA correspondence, and C-suite communications with fireproof-lockbox protocols for hardcopy. At Ascend Wellness I handled board-level governance for a publicly traded company. I treat every client's information at that standard.",
  },
  {
    q: "How is pricing structured?",
    a: "Outcome-based, never hourly. Flat fees tied to a specific deliverable. A diagnostic audit has a fixed price. A board cadence stand-up has a fixed price. A monthly retainer is priced against access and defined monthly outcomes, not hours. If I'm done in half the time, you pay the same; if it takes longer than I scoped, you still pay the same. That asymmetry is intentional.",
  },
  {
    q: "What does the first month look like?",
    a: "Week one is embedding: discovery calls, systems audit, a written diagnostic. Week two is scoping: a detailed plan for the remaining engagement with milestones. Weeks three and four are delivery against the highest-priority outcome. By day 30 you have a measurable change in the area we agreed to fix. If you don't see it, we have a conversation and I refund 100%.",
  },
];
---

<section class="bg-paper-soft py-16 md:py-24">
  <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6 md:px-10">
    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-12 gap-10 md:gap-16">
      <div class="md:col-span-4" data-reveal>
        <p class="small-caps text-copper mb-4">Real objections</p>
        <h2 class="font-display text-4xl md:text-5xl text-ink leading-[0.95] mb-5">
          The <span class="italic font-display-italic">questions</span> everyone asks.
        </h2>
        <p class="text-ink-soft text-[15px] leading-relaxed">
          Not a generic FAQ. The actual things CEOs, CFOs, and Chiefs of Staff ask on the discovery call, answered directly.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="md:col-span-8 divide-y divide-rule border-y border-rule" data-reveal>
        {qs.map((item, idx) => (
          <details class="group py-6">
            <summary class="flex items-start justify-between gap-6 cursor-pointer list-none">
              <div class="flex items-baseline gap-4 flex-1">
                <span class="font-mono text-[10px] uppercase tracking-[0.25em] text-copper tabular mt-1">0{idx + 1}</span>
                <h3 class="font-display text-xl md:text-2xl text-ink leading-snug flex-1">{item.q}</h3>
              </div>
              <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-ink-muted flex-shrink-0 mt-2 group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="1.5" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"/>
              </svg>
            </summary>
            <div class="pl-0 md:pl-12 pt-4">
              <p class="text-ink-soft text-[15px] leading-relaxed">{item.a}</p>
            </div>
          </details>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
